## Criterion 8 — Mechanism Design Documentation

**What is being evaluated:** `method.md` as the design record for the original Act IV mechanism. No execution — purely documentation assessment.

### Sub-Checks (all must pass for 5 pts)

| ID | Sub-Check | Where to Look | Pass Condition |
|----|-----------|--------------|----------------|
| H1 | Re-implementability | `method.md` | Mechanism described at a level where an engineer could **re-implement it from the document alone** (no gaps requiring guesswork) |
| H2 | Design rationale links to root cause | `method.md` | Explicitly links to the target failure mode, explaining why the mechanism addresses the **root cause** not just the surface symptom |
| H3 | Hyperparameters enumerated | `method.md` | All thresholds and parameter values **actually used** are explicitly listed with their values |
| H4 | Three ablation variants | `method.md` | Exactly **three variants** defined, each with explicit contrast to the main method (what was removed/changed, and what that tests) |
| H5 | Statistical test plan | `method.md` | Described in prose, naming: the **test name**, the **comparison being made**, and the **p-value threshold** |

### Score Tiers

#### ✅ 5 — Robust and Complete
Mechanism re-implementable from the document alone (H1). Design rationale links to target failure's root cause (H2). Hyperparameters and thresholds fully enumerated with actual values (H3). Three ablation variants defined with explicit contrasts (H4). Statistical-test plan named in prose (H5).

#### ⚠️ 3 — Correct but Incomplete
`method.md` describes the mechanism, its link to the target failure, and at least three ablations. **Missing one or more of:** sufficient depth for re-implementation, reasoned rationale, full hyperparameter enumeration, contrasted ablation variants, or prose statistical-test plan.

#### 🔴 1 — Present but Flawed
`method.md` exists with some description of the mechanism, but no design rationale, fewer than three ablations, hyperparameters absent, or no statistical framing present.

#### ⛔ 0 — Absent
No `method.md`, or the file is placeholder.

### method.md Required Structure
```markdown
## Mechanism: [Name]

### Overview
[Description sufficient for re-implementation — no gaps]

### Link to Target Failure Mode
[Why this mechanism addresses the root cause of [target failure], not just its surface]

### Hyperparameters
| Parameter | Value | Description |
|---|---|---|
| threshold_X | 0.75 | [what it controls] |
| window_days | 60 | [what it controls] |

### Ablation Variants
| Variant | What Changed | What This Tests |
|---|---|---|
| Ablation A | Removed [component X] | Whether [component X] is necessary |
| Ablation B | Changed [parameter Y] to [value] | Sensitivity to [parameter Y] |
| Ablation C | Replaced [method Z] with [baseline] | Whether [method Z] outperforms baseline |

### Statistical Test Plan
[Prose: "We will apply a [test name] comparing [group A] vs [group B] 
on [metric], with a significance threshold of p < [value]."]
```

